title: Dell G5 15 SE (2020) Review - This All-AMD Notebook Is DIFFERENT
description: The Dell G5 15 SE isn't like the other AMD gaming notebooks we've looked at in 2020.  It uses a powerful AMD Ryzen 4800H processor along with an RX 5600M graphics card instead of the RTX 2060 we usually see.  But more importantly, the Dell G5 15 SE uses AMD SmartShift technology to improve CPU and GPU benchmarks and right now there are no other notebooks with this.  But what does that mean for the G5 15 battery life, temperatures, build quality, noise and performance?  And how does it compare vs the ASUS TUF A15, MSI Bravo 15 and other gaming notebooks?  Does SmartShift even matter?  The Dell G5 15 Special Edition review is finally here!  Check out the Dell G5 15 SE -   Sponsor: Corsair ONE a100 -  Corsair ONE i200 -   Subscribe    TIMESTAMPS 0:00 - Intro 1:14 - Dell G5 15 SE Price & Specs 2:17 - G5 15 SE vs TUF A15 2:35 -  Build Quality 4:44 - Keyboard & Trackpad Performance 5:49 - Webcam (aka Potatocam) & Speakers 6:26 - Ports & I/O 7:44 - Display Color & Quality 8:48 - G5 15 SE Upgrades 9:55 - Battery Life 10:22 - AMD SmartShift Explained  12:35 -  Problems & Solutions 13:35 -  Temperatures & Acoustics 13:58 - Real World Performance & Benchmarks 15:07 - Gaming Performance & Benchmarks  16:49 - 100% Fan Speed Results 18:08 - Is the Dell G5 15 SE Worth It?  Review unit provided free of charge by Dell. This video is sponsored by Corsair's new A100. As per Hardware Canucks guidelines, no review direction was received from manufacturer.
